  "text": "On the other hand, our proposed 10 th order polyphase HB all-pass based IIR filters require only two distinct coefficients. For these filters multiplication is not required since, the coefficients of the all-pass sections are powers-of-two which can be implemented by using simple hard wired shift-and-add method without using any multipliers thus reducing the area and power consumption. The simulation results of the two aforementioned decimators when the MIT-BIH data 105 is fed into the -modulator are shown in Fig. 6 and 7 . Fig. 6 (a) illustrates the first ten seconds of the MIT-BIH data set 105, where (b) and (c) show the data at the output of the two decimation chains. On the other hand, Fig. 7 (a) and (b) show the magnitude error between data set 105 and output of the proposed decimation filter and decimation filter given in [CITATION_1] . For comparative purposes the ratio of the average power of the magnitude error to the average power of the reference input is calculated as and for the proposed decimator and the decimator given in [CITATION_2] respectively. As mentioned in the previous paragraph the number of additions and multiplications required by [CITATION_3] is much higher than our decimator. Therefore, lower magnitude error i.e. a better performance with a lower power consumption compared to what is reported in [CITATION_4] is achieved in this work.",
